webpackJsonp([0xb47c924ac32a],{351:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{wordpressPost:{title:"Hello Otter",date:"2018-06-03T22:08:53.000Z",content:'<p>Hi everyone, 👋 Email Otter wants to meet you!</p>\n<p>Email Otter is the tool I&#8217;m building that has already cut down my newsletter production from 3+ hours to less than 1. It turns static HTML email templates (<a href="https://www.emailonacid.com/blog/article/email-development/600_free_email_templates" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">like these</a>) into reusable drag and drop email components.</p>\n<p><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-682" src="http://localhost:8888/content-otter/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/8a8758c2-2d92-4561-aae7-004eb2fb8cc1-300x200.jpeg" alt="" width="300" height="200" srcset="http://localhost:8888/content-otter/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/8a8758c2-2d92-4561-aae7-004eb2fb8cc1-300x200.jpeg 300w, http://localhost:8888/content-otter/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/8a8758c2-2d92-4561-aae7-004eb2fb8cc1.jpeg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>\n<p>Editing HTML templates can be a real nightmare! I got sick of putting aside half a day (or an entire day with a hangover 🍺) for creating the weekly newsletter for <a href="http://prototypr.io/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">prototypr.io</a>. I can imagine some of you feel the same &#8211; I couldn&#8217;t find any tool to easily edit HTML templates the way I wanted &#8211; so I made my own.</p>\n<h1><strong>What it does</strong></h1>\n<p>Email otter takes care of all the mundane tasks of editing HTML emails:</p>\n<p>&#8211; Turn your HTML template into reusable modules</p>\n<p>&#8211; Automatically pull in the title, image and description for your links</p>\n<p>&#8211; Crop and compress images automatically &#8211; no more image editing tools needed!</p>\n<p>💌It&#8217;s in development at the moment but it is usable! Here&#8217;s a video of me creating my newsletter from an HTML template created with <a href="https://designmodo.com/postcards/app/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">DesignModo&#8217;s Postcards</a>:</p>\n<div class="wrapper_b5bbb"><iframe class="video_18ea7" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/9rj98_n4L9o" frameborder="0" data-mce-fragment="1"></iframe></div>\n<h1><strong>A bit on how it works</strong></h1>\n<p><strong>Convert your own templates</strong></p>\n<p>To start with Email Otter, you need to get hold of an HTML email template &#8211; you can find them all over the web. Then there&#8217;s a simple process to separate your template into HTML segments that are readable by the Otter (soon there&#8217;ll be a tool for conversion).</p>\n<p><strong>Use templates from the Otter library</strong></p>\n<p>Email Otter will come with a library of readily usable email templates and modules that you can use and combine to build your newsletters.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>🙏That&#8217;s all for this update &#8211; please get in touch if you&#8217;re interested in testing the app when it&#8217;s ready for external users!</p>\n<p>Also, you may have (not) noticed the name change. The app was previously called &#8216;Tamarin Templates&#8217; since it made use of the &#8216;<a href="https://handlebarsjs.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">handlebars</a>&#8216; templating system (and emperor monkeys have moustaches).</p>\n<p>I didn&#8217;t like that name in the end, and otters are cool, so now we have Email Otter 😃</p>\n<p><img src="https://ph-files.imgix.net/63f22358-f61f-4280-b750-2f8faef363be?auto=format&amp;auto=compress&amp;codec=mozjpeg&amp;cs=strip" alt="" /></p>\n',featured_media:{localFile:{childImageSharp:{resolutions:{src:"/blog/static/563b22b06337efce8c50140b14c743f5-eb8e58eb4d82a3afa2aeb45873c3403b-1c495.jpg",width:500,height:300},original:{width:1514,height:693,src:"/blog/static/563b22b06337efce8c50140b14c743f5-eb8e58eb4d82a3afa2aeb45873c3403b.jpg"}}}}}},pathContext:{id:"cb74b447-164e-54f4-8022-9f549f0c3327"}}}});
